description: Derived from AMOG (“alpha male of group”).

verbs.description: mog (third-person singular simple present mogs, present participle mogging, simple past and past participle mogged)

entries.meaning: (transitive, incel slang, transgender slang) To assert one's dominance over (usually in appearance).
examples: His face mogs mine to hell and back.
This youngshit mogs me: I'm such a hon.

verbs.description: mog (third-person singular simple present mogs, present participle mogging, simple past and past participle mogged)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, US, UK, dialectal) To move or walk slowly; to trudge, amble.

examples: Get that mog out of here!

verbs.description: mog (third-person singular simple present mogs, present participle mogging, simple past and past participle mogged)

entries.meaning: (transitive, Australia, informal) To remove (a public servant) from their position following a Machinery of Government change, a process in which the Government of Australia reorganizes the responsibilities and structure of the government.
